description.value: Glazed white steatite scarab in a copper alloy mount with oval base and loop handle: engraved on the base with a cartouche in the upper centre containing meaningless hieroglyphs. On either side of the cartouche, also inverted are wadjet eyes and below them uraei. Below this, in the middle register, separated by a horizontal line from the cartouche above, are two Horus falcons, between them the sign '??' (bright), flanked by 'nsw.t bity', "King of Upper and Lower Egypt". The group stands on a pedestal from the bottom of which two uraei emerge. Under the pedestal is a cord design. The copper alloy mount may be much more recent. Worn edges and deposit on seal or scarab.
